{
  "Feature_ID": "UE_CONTEXT_MODIFICATION_GNB_CU_INITIATED",
  "Feature_Name": "UE Context Modification (gNB-CU initiated)",
  "Release": "18.6.0",
  "3GPP_Reference": {
    "Spec": "TS 138.473",
    "Title": "NG-RAN; F1 Application Protocol (F1AP)",
    "Section": "8.3.4, 8.3.4.1, 8.3.4.2, 8.3.4.3, 8.3.4.4, 9.2.2.7, 9.2.2.8, 9.2.2.9"
  },
  "Feature_Description": [
    "The purpose of the UE Context Modification procedure is to modify the established UE Context, e.g., establishing, modifying and releasing radio resources or sidelink resources.",
    "This procedure is also used to command the gNB-DU to stop data transmission for the UE for mobility (see TS 38.401 [4]).",
    "The procedure uses UE-associated signalling."
  ],
  "Feature_Objectives": [
    "Modify the established UE Context.",
    "Establish radio resources.",
    "Modify radio resources.",
    "Release radio resources.",
    "Establish sidelink resources.",
    "Modify sidelink resources.",
    "Release sidelink resources.",
    "Command the gNB-DU to stop data transmission for the UE for mobility."
  ],
  "Design_Details": {
    "Protocol_Layers": [
      "F1AP"
    ],
    "Protocol_Interfaces": [
      "F1"
    ]
  },
  "Feature_Implementation_Steps": [
    "The UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION REQUEST message is initiated by the gNB-CU.",
    "Upon reception of the UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall perform the modifications.",
    "If modifications are successful, the gNB-DU reports the update in the UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION RESPONSE message.",
    "In case none of the requested modifications of the UE context can be successfully performed, the gNB-DU shall respond with the UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION FAILURE message with an appropriate cause value."
  ],
  "Call_Flow": [
    {
      "Message": "UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION REQUEST",
      "Actors": [
        "gNB-CU",
        "gNB-DU"
      ],
      "From": "gNB-CU",
      "To": "gNB-DU"
    },
    {
      "Message": "UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION RESPONSE",
      "Actors": [
        "gNB-CU",
        "gNB-DU"
      ],
      "From": "gNB-DU",
      "To": "gNB-CU"
    },
    {
      "Message": "UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION FAILURE",
      "Actors": [
        "gNB-CU",
        "gNB-DU"
      ],
      "From": "gNB-DU",
      "To": "gNB-CU"
    }
  ],
  "Procedure_Implementation_Steps": [
    "Successful Operation (8.3.4.2):",
    "1. The UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION REQUEST message is initiated by the gNB-CU.",
    "2. Upon reception of the UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall perform the modifications.",
    "3. If successful, the gNB-DU reports the update in the UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION RESPONSE message.",
    "4. Specific actions are taken by gNB-DU based on included IEs such as SpCell ID, LTM Information Modify, Conditional Intra-DU Mobility Information, SCell To Be Setup List, DRX Cycle, SRB To Be Setup List, DRB To Be Setup List, BH RLC Channel To Be Setup/Modified/Released List, Duplication Activation, RLC Duplication Information, DC Based Duplication, RRC Reconfiguration Complete Indicator, RLC Failure Indication, RRC-Container, Transmission Action Indicator, E-UTRAN QoS, DRB Information, MeasurementTimingConfiguration, MeasConfig, NeedForGapsInfoNR, NeedForGapNCSG-InfoNR, NeedForGapNCSG-InfoEUTRA, NeedForInterruptionInfoNR, CG-Config, CG-ConfigInfo, Resource Coordination Transfer Information, Subscriber Profile ID for RAT/Frequency priority, Additional RRM Policy Index, Index to RAT/Frequency Selection Priority, Uplink TxDirectCurrentList Information (and its variants), UEAssistanceInformation, UEAssistanceInformationEUTRA, Inactivity Monitoring Request, Notification Control, UL PDU Session Aggregate Maximum Bit Rate, gNB-DU UE Aggregate Maximum Bit Rate Uplink, GNB-DU Configuration Query, Bearer Type Change, NeedforGap, QoS Flow Mapping Indication, Lower Layer presence status change, Full Configuration, QoS Monitoring Request, NR/LTE V2X/A2X Services Authorized, LTE/NR UE Sidelink Aggregate Maximum Bit Rate (for V2X/A2X), PC5 Link Aggregate Maximum Bit Rate, TSC Traffic Characteristics, CPAC MCG Information, S-CPAC Request, Transmission Stop Indicator, SCG Indicator, Estimated Arrival Probability, Location Measurement Information, F1-C Transfer Path NRDC, ENB DL Transport Layer Address, PDCP Terminating Node DL Transport Layer Address, IAB Conditional RRC Message Delivery Indication, MDT Polluted Measurement Indicator, SCG Activation Request, CG-SDT Query Indication, 5G ProSe Authorized, SDT Bearer Configuration Query Indication, 5G ProSe UE PC5 Aggregate Maximum Bit Rate, 5G ProSe PC5 Link Aggregate Bit Rate, Updated Remote UE Local ID, Uu RLC Channel To Be Setup/Modified/Release List, PC5 RLC Channel To Be Setup/Modified/Release List, Path Switch Configuration, MUSIM-GapConfig, gNB-DU UE Slice Maximum Bit Rate List, Multicast MBS Session Setup/Remove List, UE Multicast MRB To Be Setup at Modify List, MBS PTP Retransmission Tunnel Required, MBS PTP Forwarding Tunnel Required Information, Management Based MDT PLMN Modification List, PDU Set QoS Parameters, ECN Marking or Congestion Information Reporting Request, MBSInterestIndication, Network Controlled Repeater Authorized, LTM Indicator, Request for Lower Layer Configuration, Reference Configuration Information, CSI Resource Configuration, LTM Configuration ID Mapping List, Early Sync Information Request, Early Sync Candidate Cell Information List, UE Based TA Measurement Configuration, Early Sync Serving Cell Information, LTM CFRA Resource Config List, LTM Cells to be Released List, LTM Reset Information, Direct Path Addition, Indirect Path Addition, N3C Indirect Path Addition, S-NSSAI, S-CPAC Lower Layer Reference Config Request, musim-CandidateBandList, DL LBT Failure Information Request, Ranging and Sidelink Positioning Service Information, SDT Volume Threshold.",
    "Unsuccessful Operation (8.3.4.3):",
    "1. In case none of the requested modifications of the UE context can be successfully performed, the gNB-DU shall respond with the UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION FAILURE message with an appropriate cause value.",
    "2. If the Conditional Intra-DU Mobility Information IE was included in the UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION REQUEST message and set to \"CHO-initiation\", the gNB-DU shall include the received SpCell ID IE as the Requested Target Cell ID IE in the UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION FAILURE message.",
    "3. If the gNB-DU is not able to accept the SpCell ID IE in UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION REQUEST message, it shall reply with the UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION FAILURE message.",
    "4. If the Conditional Intra-DU Mobility Information IE was included and set to \"CHO-initiation\" or \"CHO-replace\", but the SpCell ID IE was not included in the UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall respond with the UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION FAILURE message with an appropriate cause value.",
    "5. If the LTM Information Modify IE was included, but the SpCell ID IE and the CSI Resource Configuration IE were not included in the UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall respond with the UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION FAILURE message with an appropriate cause value.",
    "6. If the gNB-DU is not able to accept the UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION REQUEST message for mobility because an LTM command has been triggered to the UE, it shall reply with the UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION FAILURE message with an appropriate cause value.",
    "Abnormal Conditions (8.3.4.4):",
    "1. If the gNB-DU receives a UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION REQUEST message containing a E-UTRAN QoS IE for a GBR QoS DRB but where the GBR QoS Information IE is not present, the gNB-DU shall report the establishment of the corresponding DRB as failed in the DRB Failed to Setup List IE of the UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION RESPONSE message with an appropriate cause value.",
    "2. If the gNB-DU receives a UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION REQUEST message containing a DRB QoS IE for a GBR QoS DRB but where the GBR QoS Flow Information IE is not present, the gNB-DU shall report the establishment of the corresponding DRBs as failed in the DRB Failed to Setup List IE of the UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION RESPONSE message with an appropriate cause value.",
    "3. If the Delay Critical IE is included in the Dynamic 5QI Descriptor IE within the DRB QoS IE in the UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION REQUEST message and is set to the value \"delay critical\" but the Maximum Data Burst Volume IE is not present, the gNB-DU shall report the establishment of the corresponding DRB as failed in the DRB Failed to Setup List IE of the of the UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION RESPONSE message with an appropriate cause value.",
    "4. If one or more candidate cells in the Candidate Cells To Be Cancelled List IE included in the UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION REQUEST message were not prepared using the same UE-associated signaling connection, the gNB-DU shall ignore those non-associated candidate cells."
  ],
